HEADWORD: Unau
<hw>U*nau"</hw> <pr>(⟦usl⟧*n⟦add⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Brazilian.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The two-toed sloth
(<spn>Cholopus didactylus</spn>), native of South America. It is about
two feet long. Its color is a uniform grayish brown, sometimes with a
reddish tint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

